history.content: I'm pretty sure there's a reserve right now on the open seats, likely because the new Data Science major is coming in Spring of 2018, and there are holds on all sorts of Data Science courses likely to facilitate juniors and seniors interested in declaring the major. That said, I'd assume you're in a good position to get in. Just follow up when the adjustment period opens, and keep your fingers crossed :-)

I am waitlisted as #13 for CS 88 but noticed there are only 80/112 people enrolled in the class right now. Does this mean there are more seats that will open up?/do I have a good chance of getting in?
